<h3>Why do we have it?</h3>
<p>We collect Members&rsquo; personal profile information for various purposes but only relating to the business operations in our Marketplace.&nbsp; Personal name and contact details are required to identify individuals. Collecting Driver licence numbers allows us to uniquely identify embers and qualify them as Carriers. The Company name and contact details allows for proper qualification of the corporate entities being paid or issued with credit terms. Industry relevant numbers, e.g. National Safety Code numbers, verifies security to other Members that the services being rendered are being provided by qualified providers. Other kinds of personal profile information are either required for basic functionality (e.g. email communications) or to enable networking features on the platform (e.g. connecting with other members).</p>
<h3>Where does it come from?</h3>
<p>A member&rsquo;s profile information is provided manually by the Member during and after registration and account set-up. This process may be automatic in future, e.g. if using other tools for login credentials or government databases.</p>
<p>The member&rsquo;s Reputation is a representation based on feedback from other members who have engaged in business activity with that member. Also, various performance data points collected by <em>Go99</em>&trade; (e.g. number of loads delivered) may be displayed.</p>
<h3>Who can see it?</h3>
<p><em>Go99</em>&trade; members are able to view other member profiles in order to make business related decisions. Before engaging in business with another party, the profiles allow for business risk to be calculated.</p>
<p>Only members with the appropriate permissions can see financial data.</p>
<h3>Who sees Transaction Data?</h3>
<p>Shippers see what Carriers quote; Carriers see what Shippers pay.&nbsp; Only the parties engaged in the specific transaction will have visibility of the information relevant to their role that transaction.</p>
<h3>Who it is shared with?</h3>
<p>Other members of the <em>Go99</em>&trade; system may view your profile.&nbsp; Transaction data is only shared with service providers who require the information to make payments to, or make collections from, members conducting business transactions in the Marketplace. Before being shared, all unnecessary personal identifiers are removed from the data and anonymized using industry standards.</p>
