<h1>#Finance Fee and Payment Calculations</h1>
<p>The <em>Go99</em>&trade; digital freight matching Marketplace allows for clear and transparent financial transactions &ndash; we do not get between Shippers and Carriers &ndash; Shippers see what Carriers quote and Carriers see what Shippers pay.</p>
<p>There are NO subscriptions, transaction fees, access fees, membership dues, or data purchases for basic use of the platform. Neither Shippers, nor Carriers pay to access our free and transparent Marketplace.</p>
<h2>What is the Normal Workflow for a Transaction?</h2>
<div class="term-center">
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>Shipper makes a Service Request (posts a load)</p>
  <p>Carriers submit quotes (not seen by other Carriers)</p>
  <p>Shipper reviews quotes and Reputation Scores of Carriers</p>
  <p>Shipper assigns the Service Request to a Carrier &ndash; Enters a Contract of Carriage</p>
  <p>Carrier picks up, transports and delivers the load</p>
  <p>Upon receipt of a &ldquo;Received in good order&rdquo; report, the following cascade is initiated:</p>
  <p><strong>First</strong>: Payment is initiated to the Carrier for NextDayPay<a href="#_ftn1" name="_ftnref1">[1]</a>,</p>
  <p><strong>Then</strong>: an Invoice is submitted to the Carrier for payment</p>
</div>
<h2>How are the Payments and Invoices Calculated?</h2>
