<h1>#Reputation, Feedback and Member Comments</h1>
<p>Your business is built on the back of your reputation &ndash; we believe you should be rewarded for maintaining a good one!&nbsp; Your reputation is an important measure of the quality on the <em>Go99</em>&trade; platform.&nbsp; Our Reputation Management System&trade; (knows as the RMS&trade;) will allow you to build a reputation that you are proud of and one that gets you the respect you deserve.</p>
<p>The <em>Go99</em>&trade; experience should be quick, easy and efficient for everyone involved. That&rsquo;s why after every delivery, we ask that the shipper/receiving party and the driver are asked to leave a Reputation Score and Feedback. In return, Drivers and Carriers are able to leave a Score and Feedback also.</p>
<p>Your Reputation will be shown in your profile for you to monitor and for your clients and service providers to view.&nbsp; For this reason we encourage all members to monitor their reputation closely.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Your Reputation is built on three things: (i) Reputation Score, (ii) Measurable Criteria based on your performance, and (iii) Comments from other members you engage in business with.</p>
<h2>What are the Measurable Criteria and how are they displayed?</h2>
<p>Our system will be recording your activity within our system environment. This will include things like Miles Travelled, Loaded Miles, Number of Deliveries, Number of Disputes, and similar.&nbsp; These facts will be displayed objectively, without any manipulation by additional factors.&nbsp; Our system may reward members for reaching certain milestones with &ldquo;badge icons&rdquo; visible on their profiles.</p>
<h2>What is a Reputation Score and how is it calculated?</h2>
<p>Only members you have engaged in business with can contribute to your Reputation Score.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Your overall Reputation Score is an average of the individual Reputation Scores contributed by the 200 or fewer most recent members you have engaged in business with. Simply, if you have completed less than 200 deliveries, your Score is calculated by adding up all the individual Scores and dividing that number by the number of Scores you have received. Example:</p>
<div class="term-center">
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>(added total of all your scores)</p>
  <p>&divide;</p>
  <p>(total number of scores)</p>
  <p>=</p>
  <p>your <em>Go99</em>&trade; Reputation Score</p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>If you've completed more than 200 trips, your score is calculated like this:</p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p>(added total of scores from last 200 deliveries)</p>
  <p>&divide;</p>
  <p>(200)</p>
  <p>=</p>
  <p>your <em>Go99</em>&trade; Reputation Score</p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<h3>Scores change quickly and often with every delivery at first</h3>
<p>All members start with a blank slate &ndash; that&rsquo;s the level playing field.&nbsp; Your profile won&rsquo;t show a Reputation Score until you have completed 10 deliveries and received Reputation Scores from the Shipper/Receiving Party.&nbsp; Your Score will change often and quickly until you have made between 50-100 Scored Deliveries &ndash; because there are fewer Scores to add together and average.</p>
<h3>What is included in the Reputation Score?</h3>
<p>Your average Score includes deliveries where the Shipper/Carrier provided a Score. Shippers/Carriers have the option not to provide a Score, but they are strongly encouraged to do so &ndash; it strengthens the reliability of the platform and maintains the highest quality possible. Most Shippers/Carriers will provide a Score, but if they don&rsquo;t, that delivery will not contribute to your overall Reputation Score. Shippers/Carriers have several days to provide a Score which is why you may see your score change on days you are not delivering or shipping loads.</p>
<p>Remembers that only your last 200 Scores contribute to your overall Reputation Score. So, if you have completed more than 200 Scores deliveries, only the most recent 200 count toward your overall Reputation Score.</p>
<h3>Why is the Reputation Score so important?</h3>
<p>Your Reputation is one of the only things you can truly control in your business &ndash; make it count!</p>
<p>Your overall Reputation Score is one important way that <em>Go99</em>&trade; and those you do business with can evaluate your performance and your partnership. Sometimes, members&rsquo; accounts will be deactivated due to consistently low Reputation Score. This ensures that <em>Go99</em>&trade; members continue to receive a high-quality service and experience. We find that members who consistently provide a high Score of those they engage in business with are more active within the Marketplace and refer other Shippers and Carries to our platform.&nbsp;</p>
<p>The result is more loads and better paying loads in the marketplace as well as more and better quality Carriers/Driver providing services.</p>
<h2>How are Comments made and who is responsible for them?</h2>
<p>Only members you have engaged in business with can leave Comments based on their experience throughout a specific transaction with you. The purpose of this is to allow members to make informed decisions about whether they want to enter into a transaction with you or another member.</p>
<p>Following each successful delivery, both parties are invited to leave a Comment based on their experience of the other throughout the transaction &ndash; Comments should be a critical appraisal of the experience, with the intent to highlight a particular level of skill or to provide guidance on how to improve the level of service and experience for the other party.</p>
<p>You are ultimately responsible for all the comments you leave, as well as how they are interpreted by other members.&nbsp; Be careful to leave appropriate Comments with appropriate content.</p>
<h3>Feedback comments containing inappropriate content</h3>
<p>Feedback and Comments containing content deemed by <em>Go99</em>&trade; to be inappropriate content may include content which violates applicable laws, is discriminatory, cannot be reasonably verified, is abusive or appears to have a purpose not intended by <em>Go99</em>&trade;.</p>
<h4>These types of Feedback Comments may be removed or edited:</h4>
<p>Feedback containing personally identifying information about another member, such as a member's address, phone number, email address, or real name. We may also remove Feedback that can be used to obtain personally identifying information about another member, such as a shipment tracking number.</p>
<p>Feedback not related to a load transaction, including a comment, reply, or follow-up related to a different load.</p>
<p>Feedback Comments containing political, religious, social, or other commentary, rather than genuine comments about a load.</p>
<p>Feedback Comments containing language that is profane, vulgar, obscene, discriminatory either sexist or racist, as well as Comments containing age-restricted material or physical threats.</p>
<p>Feedback Comments containing links or promotional language which encourages Members to engage outside of <em>Go99</em> &trade;.</p>
<p>Feedback Comments that includes references to current or previous law enforcement investigations or <em>Go99</em>&trade; investigations.</p>
<p>Feedback Comments containing URLs or links outside <em>Go99</em>&trade;-owned and operated domains.</p>
<h4>These types of Feedback Comments aren't removed:</h4>
<p>Feedback comments containing accusatory language such as "fraud," "liar," "cheater," "scam artist," or "con man." Although this type of comment is strongly discouraged, it isn't removed unless it also contains content that isn't allowed.</p>
